            <fr:title text="Markov's Principle">Markov's Principle</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Markov's Principle is a weak choice principle, weaker than the law of excluded middle.
It can be formulated in many equivalent ways:
<html:ol><html:li>Any sequence of booleans <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N} \to  \mathbb {B}]]></fr:tex> that is not always 0 must contain a 1.</html:li>
<html:li>The <fr:link href="/VWNF/" title="Extended Natural Numbers" uri="https://um-catlab.github.io/VWNF/" display-uri="VWNF" type="local">extended natural numbers</fr:link> are equivalent to the natural numbers with a point adjoined. More precisely, the inclusion <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\uplus \{\Omega \} \to  \mathbb {N}_\infty ]]></fr:tex> is surjective (and thus a bijection).</html:li></html:ol></html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
